Lebanon on Monday signed an agreement with the Food and Agriculture Organisation (FAO) of the United Nations, aimed at supporting small farmers to ensure their resilience amid the current economic crisis, the National News Agency reported. Lebanese Agriculture Minister Abbas Mortada said this at a meeting with the FAO Representative in Lebanon, Maurice Saade. “The agreement aims at launching a project that would support the production of organic fertilizer, high quality and environmentally sound forage crops to replace chemical fertilizer and imported animal feed,” Mortada said. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Mortada noted that the current tough economic situation necessitates continuous work to support farmers and productive sectors. Meanwhile, Saade said that FAO was keen to stand by Lebanon’s Agriculture Ministry and all parties providing support for Lebanese farmers. (Xinhua/NAN)